  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-06-24",
    "date": "2021-12-07T16:57:36Z",
    "text": "Healthcare Opportunities for Patriots in Exile Act or the HOPE Act\n\nThis bill authorizes the Department of Homeland Security to parole into the United States an alien veteran who (1) is seeking temporary admission to receive health care from the Department of Veterans Affairs, and (2) is outside the United States after having been ordered removed or voluntarily departed from the United States.\n\nSuch parole may not be available for an alien who is inadmissible due to a criminal conviction for a crime of violence, excluding a purely political offense, or a crime that endangers U.S. national security, for which the alien has served at least five years in prison."
  },
